<b>EMI Calculator</b>
<p>The emi calculator takes loan amount as input, Interest rate as input, term as input.</p>
<p> Applies formula for compound Interest Calculation</p>
<h>formula is A = p(1+r/n*100)^n</h>




import numpy_financial as npf # pyright: ignore[reportMissingImports]
def EmiCalculator(p, r, n) ->float:
    
    r = r/(12*100)
    n = n*12
    emi = p*r*(((1 + r)**n)/((1 + r)**n - 1))
    #emi = a/(n)
    return (round(emi,2))
